<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-061-067 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 278 013</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Sept 10 1991 v5 n30 p6(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Micro Planning replaces standby with new entry-level Manager.andO;(Micro Planning International Inc.'s Manager project-managementpackage replaces its Micro Planner application) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Garner, Rochelle.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Micro Planning International Inc introduces the Managerproject-management software package, which replaces the company'sMicro Planner application.andP;  The entry-level Manager programhandles as many as five sub-projects and as many as 1,500activities; information and reports created by the $595 programcan be sent over the network to Micro Planning's X-Pert high-endprogram for professional project managers.andP;  Among Manager'sfeatures are Gantt, PERT, outline and spreadsheet views; use of adesktop metaphor much like that used in the Macintosh; the abilityto schedule tasks by deadlines, target start and finish dates,fixed start and finish dates, and just-in-time; hot links similarto System 7.0's publish and subscribe; and the ability to perform'what-if' analyses by examining the effects of leveling time orresource conflicts.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Micro Planning International Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Manager (Project management software) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionProject ManagementSoftware PackagesLow Cost.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Rochelle GarnerandM;Mill Valley, Calif.andP;  -- Micro Planning International Inc., among the firstplayers in the Macintosh project-management market, next week will ship a newentry-level program that promises ease of use and greater flexibility inmanaging smaller projects.andM;Replacing the venerable Micro Planner application, the new $595 Manager willhandle up to five subprojects and up to 1,500 activities.andP;  All informationand reports created in Manager can be sent over the network to X-Pert, thecompany's high-end program for professional project managers.andM;&quot;Manager's ease of use is significantly better than with Micro Planner 6,&quot;said Doug Morlock, systems engineer for the U.S.andP;  Army at Picatinny Arsenal,N.J.andP;  &quot;It's non-esoteric where possible, and it is made for people who don'tnecessarily have a master's degree in project management.&quot;andM;Features include:andM;andgt;Views.andP;  Manager offers Gantt, PERT, outline and spreadsheet views.andP;  A workbreakdown structure (WBS) tree lets managers graphically summarizeinformation related to multiple projects.andP;  Views can be tiled on-screen,allowing users to see different charts at the same time.andP;  Data can be enteredin any view.andM;andgt;Inner desktop.andP;  When starting Manager, users see a desktop similar to thatof the Mac.andP;  When users generate new reports, report templates or charts, theprogram automatically creates documents on the desktop.andP;  The desktop metaphoralso applies to customizing menus.andP;  Simply placing a document in a reportsfolder, for example, adds that document to the menu for easy access.andM;andgt;Scheduling.andP;  Users can schedule tasks by deadlines, target start and finishdates, fixed start and finish dates, and as &quot;just in time.&quot; The programhandles an unlimited number of links per activity and links between projects.andO;It supports both arrow and precedence scheduling methods.andM;andgt;Hot links.andP;  Manager offers a hot-links feature similar to System 7.0'spublish and subscribe.andP;  Users can, for example, transmit live reports anddata over a network to an X-Pert user overseeing multiple projects.andO;Transmitted information must be on a shared volume.andP;  X-Pert users receive theinformation by defining the path to follow over the network.andM;andgt;Resource leveling.andP;  Manager lets users quickly perform &quot;what-if&quot; analyses byexamining the effects of leveling time or resource conflicts.andP;  Resources canbe split among tasks; task durations can be adjusted.andM;Site licenses and volume discounts are available.andM;Micro Planning International Inc. is at 655 Redwood Highway, Suite 311, MillValley, Calif.andP;  94941.andP;  Phone (415) 389-1420; fax (415) 389-8046.andO;</TEXT></DOC>